ushi (usable shell init) is an init system forked from kisslinux init system

WIP, do not attempt to use yet

-bin
|-init        : symlink to ../lib/ushi/init
|-ushi        : ushi service manager
|-kall.c      : c program for killing all process (used by init)
|-kpow.c      : c program for powering of the kernel
|-poweroff    : poweroff command for ushi
\-reboot      : reboot command for ushi

-lib
\-ushi
 |-init       : init, pid 1
 |-libushi    : library loaded by init, this might get removed / revamped
 |-services   : directory for the all the services
 |\-TODO
 \-enabled    : directory runlevel directories with symlinks to enabled services
  |-sysinit   : scripts 
  |-boot      : scripts 
  |-default   : scripts 
  |-post      : scripts 
  |-powerdown : scripts 
  |-poweroff  : scripts 
  \-reboot    : scripts 
